"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:5.8\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">5.8</span> 标题：脚凳（footstool）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：הֲדֹם, רֶגֶל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：hadom regel)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:2\">1CH 28:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:5\">PSA 99:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:7\">PSA 132:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:1\">ISA 66:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:1\">LAM 2:1</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：כֶּבֶשׁ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：kevesh)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:18\">2CH 9:18</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ὑποπόδιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：hupopodion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:35\">MAT 5:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:43\">LUK 20:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:35\">ACT 2:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:49\">ACT 7:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:13\">HEB 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:13\">HEB 10:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:3\">JAS 2:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Latin</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">拉：scabillum</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Esd6:4\">2ES 6:4</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0477_footstool.jpg\" alt=\"国王脚踏脚凳而坐（拉吉浮雕）\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">国王脚踏脚凳而坐（拉吉浮雕） (© Zunkir, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>脚凳是一种供人放脚的家具，形状像一张矮凳，人可以把双脚放在上面，使脚离开地面。埃及人的脚凳描绘的是埃及王击败的敌人，如插图所示。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/PTZ-0084_footstool.jpg\" alt=\"这个皇家脚凳上有国王敌人的图像，他可以把脚放在上面\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">这个皇家脚凳上有国王敌人的图像，他可以把脚放在上面 (© Ray Pritz by United Bible Societies)</figcaption></figure>脚凳在世界许多地方都是一种常见的人文现象，因此有时不必使用描述性的短语。然而，翻译者可以采用“用来放脚的东西”等类表达。在有些语言中，“脚凳”的功能对等词是“脚棍”；脚棍是一种架高的搁脚棍子，免得双脚直接踩在普通房子或棚屋里面相对潮湿的泥地上。</p>\n<p>除了<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:3\">JAS 2:3</a> 以外，希腊文<em>hupopodion</em> 在新约中仅作为比喻出现。这个词出现在新约对旧约经文的直接或间接引用中。我们查阅的大多数译本都是按照字面意思来翻译这个词的；例如，在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:43\">LUK 20:43</a> 中，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 英文意为，“等我把你的仇敌作为脚凳放在你的脚下。”<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> 没有译成比喻，英文意为“等我把你的仇敌置于你的控制之下”。同样地，在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:35\">MAT 3:35</a> 中，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> 并没有按照原文字面翻译成“也不可指着地起誓，因为地是他的脚凳”（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> ），英文的意思是，“使用地的名称，因为地属于上帝。”在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:3\">JAS 2:3</a> 中，主人侮辱穷人，让他“坐在我脚凳下”，这里的<em>hupopodion</em> 一词指的是真正的脚凳。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> 在译文中保留了“脚凳”一词，英文意为“坐在我脚凳旁边的地上”。然而，大多数译本都省略了脚凳，采用了类似<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 的译法，“坐在我脚边的地上”。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
